My meme

This meme is based on my personal earliest experiences in the world of computer science. It is the beginning of a string of woes and frustration for every aspiring computer science student.

The meme

library(magick)

# Creates the title/caption of the meme

title <- image_blank(width = 530,
                     height = 80,
                     color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "MFW first encountering floating-point error",
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 29,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

# Creating the first literal layer of the meme

floating_point_input <- image_read("https://images2.imgbox.com/f1/ee/16GB6VLK_o.png") %>%
  image_scale("280x250!")

neutral_npc <- image_read("https://images2.imgbox.com/69/38/Ba0Gj7ap_o.png") %>%
  image_scale("250x250!")

first_row <- c(floating_point_input, neutral_npc) %>%
  image_append

# Creating the second literal layer of the meme

floating_point_output <- image_read("https://images2.imgbox.com/98/a8/fzVOCHgy_o.png") %>%
  image_scale("280x250!")

angry_npc <- image_read("https://images2.imgbox.com/bb/79/zqAp0vxG_o.png") %>%
  image_scale("250x250!")

second_layer <- c(floating_point_output, angry_npc) %>%
  image_append

# Stacking all layers together to create the final product and saving

final <- c(title, first_row, second_layer) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE) %>%
  image_write("my_meme.png")

My animated GIF

As a person who is chronically online, the GIF created is a personal, generalized yet accurate description of every Internet dispute.

The GIF

library(magick)

# Creating all the frames

frame1 <- image_blank(660,
                      430,
                      color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Every Internet\nArgument",
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 80,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

frame2 <- image_read("https://images2.imgbox.com/5c/73/99kecTMJ_o.png") %>%
  image_scale("660x430!")

frame3 <- image_read("https://images2.imgbox.com/90/f2/GUfgFzBq_o.png") %>%
  image_scale("660x430!")

frame4 <- image_read("https://images2.imgbox.com/42/73/246iLcIY_o.png") %>%
  image_scale("660x430!")

frame5 <- image_read("https://images2.imgbox.com/23/d2/WJngD8FS_o.png") %>%
  image_scale("660x430!")

frame6 <- image_read("https://images2.imgbox.com/17/71/78TfM1To_o.png") %>%
  image_scale("660x430!")

frame7 <- image_read("https://images2.imgbox.com/9c/e0/1dnb2LcG_o.png") %>%
  image_scale("660x430!")

# Creating and saving the GIF

final_gif <- c(frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4, frame5, frame6, frame7) %>%
  image_animate(fps = 0.5) %>%
  image_write("my_animation.gif")
